The paper proposes an evolutionary many-objective optimization algorithm, which falls under the category of optimization and search algorithms. The algorithm is based on corner solution search, which involves identifying the boundaries of Pareto fronts. This suggests that the paper could belong to the following sub-categories:

- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): This sub-category deals with the development and application of neural networks and evolutionary algorithms, which are relevant to the proposed algorithm.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): This sub-category covers a wide range of topics related to AI, including optimization algorithms. The proposed algorithm could be considered as an AI-based optimization algorithm.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): This sub-category focuses on the development and application of machine learning algorithms, which could be relevant to the proposed algorithm.
- cs.DM (Data Mining): This sub-category deals with the extraction of useful information from large datasets, which could be relevant to the optimization problems addressed in the paper.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): This sub-category covers topics related to the modeling, analysis, and control of complex systems, which could be relevant to the real-world engineering optimization problems addressed in the paper.
